Source: Austral English
Author: MORRIS
Vol / Page: 75
Edition:
Quote: <i>Cabbage Tree</i> ... (1) Name given to various palm trees of which the heart of the young leaves is eaten like the head of a cabbage. In Australia the name is applied to the fan palm, <i>Livistona inermis</i>, R. Br., and more commonly to <i>Livistona australis</i>, Martius. In New Zealand the name is given to varius species of Cordyline, especially to <i>Cordyline indiovisa. </i>
